tourBios.otherInfo: BUY.COM TOUR member 1996-97 and 1999-2000...made the cut in 13 of 21 events in 1999 with three top-10 finishes...enjoyed solid five-week stretch beginning at the Knoxville Open, where he was T4 after 54 holes, but closing 74 dropped him to T12...tied for 10th the following week at the Cleveland Open where he posted a final-round 67...missed the cut the following week at the U. S. Open at Pinehurtt...Came back to challenge for titles in his next two events, finishing T4 at both the Lehigh Valley Open and the Hershey Open...ranked fifth in Third Round Scoring Average (69.62) and seventh in Greens in Regulation Percentage (70.0%)...played in 26 events in 1997 with nine cuts made and two top-10 finishes...registered back-to-back T5 finishes at the Hershey Open and the Laurel Creek Classic...nonexempt member in 1996...involved in auto accident in early 1996, with injuries including broken right ankle and broken hand...qualified for the 1991 U. S. Open at Hazeltine National Golf Club, where he missed the cut...winner of 13 mini-tour events.

dyn.dynResults: He has finished 4th on the Web.com Tour 2 times.
